15 Section 1. Section 15-24-1207, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "15-24-1207. Reporting requirements -- penalty -- rules. (1) Each private person who is a
17 possessor or a beneficial user of tax-exempt property for industrial, trade, or other business purposes subject to
18 tax pursuant to 15-24-1203 shall, on or before March 1 each year, file with the department a statement of the
19 possession or other beneficial use of tax-exempt property in the preceding calendar year and the value of the
20 property. The statement must be in the form prescribed by the department and must be verified by the
21 possessor or beneficial user or, in the case of an association or corporation, by an officer of the association or
22 corporation. The statement must include:
23 (a) the name and address of the person, association, or corporation;
24 (b) the location of the tax-exempt property; and
25 (c) the market value in dollars and cents of the tax-exempt property.
26 (2) Entities listed in 15-6-201(1)(a) that lease or otherwise allow the possession or beneficial use of
27 tax-exempt property for industrial, trade, or other business purposes shall file an annual report with the
28 department. The report must include the following information for each lease or agreement:
